<body>
	<h1>This is a Test for the Functionalities of the PHI-core Plugin</h1>
	<h2>ID Generator</h2>
	<p>
		<span class="highlighted">
			PHI.id(prefix, length) 
		</span>
		- Generate a random ID, composed by the string "phi-", the string <i>prefix</i>, if not empty, followed by a minus ( {prefix}- ), and a radomized number of 10 digits or, 
		if length is not empty, of the length passed.<br />
		While generating the ID, the partial value is fetched through an array which contains every IDs generated, so a replication is not possible. 
	</p>
	<h3>Parameters</h3>
	<ul>
		<li>prefix - string: a string used to customize the ID</li>
		<li>length - integer: the length o the final part of the ID</li>
	</ul>
	<h3>Return</h3>
	<ul>
		<li>
			string: the unique generated ID
		</li>
	</ul>
	<h3>Examples</h3>
	<p>
		Generation of a sample ID:
		<code>PHI.id();</code> - Result: <span id = "Result1"></span>
	</p>
	<p>
		Generation of an ID with prefix:
		<code>PHI.id("test");</code> - Result: <span id = "Result2"></span>
	</p>
	<p>
		Generation of an ID with prefix and fixed length:
		<code>PHI.id("test", 5);</code> - Result: <span id = "Result3"></span>
	</p>
	<script type="text/javascript">
		window.addEvent("domready", function(){
			document.id("Result1").set('html', PHI.id());
			document.id("Result2").set('html', PHI.id("test"));
			document.id("Result3").set('html', PHI.id("test", 5));
		});
	</script>
</body>
</html>